Alternative forms[edit]

  • worpiō, guerpiō, gurpiō

Etymology[edit]

Borrowed from Frankish *werpijan (“to throw (away), cast off”).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈwer.pi.oː/, [ˈwɛr.pi.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈver.pi.o/, [ˈvɛr.pi.ɔ]

Verb[edit]

werpiō (present infinitive werpīre, perfect active werpīvī, supine werpītum); fourth conjugation

  1. I forgo, waive
  2. I denounce, disavow, abandon
  3. I divorce
